1
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:22,370
Commander, we found an inn ahead.

2
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:24,460
It's located on the only route
to Bailejing.

3
00:00:24,460 --> 00:00:26,690
We should be able to get information
about Bailejing there.

4
00:00:26,690 --> 00:00:29,940
Adjutant Zhang, go and scout ahead.

5
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:34,370
Understood.

6
00:00:56,570 --> 00:00:57,740
Coming.

7
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:03,270
It's so late, and there are still people
coming here to die?

8
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:05,069
You guys go hide first, quickly.

9
00:01:05,209 --> 00:01:05,930
Coming!

10
00:01:10,350 --> 00:01:11,730
In the dead of night...

11
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,410
Sirs, are you here for a stay?

12
00:01:27,070 --> 00:01:27,730
Sirs.

13
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:46,539
Officers,

14
00:01:46,570 --> 00:01:47,830
do you want some rooms?

15
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,900
How many people can this place hold?

16
00:01:51,210 --> 00:01:51,940
My little inn

17
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:53,570
can hold over 30 people.

18
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,280
We'll book the whole place.

19
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:04,230
The whole place?

20
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:06,630
There are only 4 of you.

21
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,889
I'm afraid you won't be able to fill it.

22
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,800
Okay, okay.

23
00:02:18,829 --> 00:02:20,910
I'm going to discuss it
with the guests now.

24
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,220
Please sit and wait for a while.

25
00:02:22,220 --> 00:02:24,880
We'll serve you
nice food and wine immediately.

26
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:26,579
Please take your seats.

27
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:40,250
Just 4 soldiers.

28
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:41,300
Let's kill them.

29
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:44,500
They don't look like Nanqiang warlords.

30
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,990
I think they should be scouts.

31
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:47,100
If we wipe them out,

32
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:48,390
no one should find out.

33
00:02:48,579 --> 00:02:49,590
Let's kill them

34
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,410
after they collapse.

35
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:50,860
Okay.

36
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,220
The Chief just told us

37
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,050
to turn over a new leaf.

38
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:56,970
How does the saying go?

39
00:02:58,370 --> 00:02:59,500
"Only kill bad people,

40
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,810
not good ones."

41
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:01,970
Besides,

42
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,780
these soldiers are no pushovers.

43
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,550
But there are knockout drops in the water.

44
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:08,480
Knockout drops?

45
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:12,740
Adjutant Zhang,

46
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:14,580
I heard you used to be

47
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:16,800
a member of the Southern Archives.

48
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,870
It seems that the two of us

49
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,960
do have quite a bit of fate between us.

50
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:24,750
I have a very excellent memory.

51
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,300
Captain Chen,

52
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,360
I think we haven't met before, right?

53
00:03:31,410 --> 00:03:32,610
How should I put it?

54
00:03:32,850 --> 00:03:34,540
When I was in Nanyang,

55
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:36,880
I killed all the people in your Archives.

56
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,800
And you killed all my men

57
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,740
in our Xiaojiang camp.

58
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:43,800
I'm wondering

59
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,650
if this is also a kind

60
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:47,100
of special destiny.

61
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:53,530
The people of the Southern Archives

62
00:03:53,530 --> 00:03:55,180
acted very covertly.

63
00:03:56,030 --> 00:03:57,829
They were just like mice,

64
00:03:57,850 --> 00:03:59,079
hard to find

65
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,500
and kill.

66
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:02,580
Therefore,

67
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,220
killing them

68
00:04:04,860 --> 00:04:07,060
gave me a greater sense of achievement.

69
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,890
Why don't you tell me more about

70
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:32,450
how you killed them?

71
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,430
If you really want to hear about it,

72
00:04:48,659 --> 00:04:49,860
I'll tell you.

73
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:53,540
I

74
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:55,180
have

75
00:04:55,570 --> 00:04:56,930
a little hobby.

76
00:04:57,620 --> 00:04:58,540
I like

77
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,360
to collect pretty human skin.

78
00:05:01,730 --> 00:05:04,290
I especially like the exquisite, tattooed

79
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,060
human skin of the staff

80
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,290
from your Archives.

81
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:13,860
Every time I caught them,

82
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,630
I used a knife

83
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:17,190
to cut a cross

84
00:05:17,490 --> 00:05:19,490
on the top of their heads.

85
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:21,370
And then,

86
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:23,170
I slowly poured

87
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:25,410
mercury in,

88
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:28,660
so their blood

89
00:05:28,890 --> 00:05:30,380
would help the mercury

90
00:05:30,620 --> 00:05:32,380
spread all over their bodies.

91
00:05:32,450 --> 00:05:33,240
At this step,

92
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:37,460
I could listen to their screams

93
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,990
while watching their skin and muscles

94
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:41,210
separate naturally.

95
00:05:41,690 --> 00:05:43,250
When the time was about right,

96
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:44,510
I peeled off their skin

97
00:05:45,130 --> 00:05:46,590
little by little,

98
00:05:46,770 --> 00:05:48,830
starting from the top of their heads.

99
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:51,390
There was a requirement

100
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:53,250
in this.

101
00:05:54,010 --> 00:05:55,670
After the skin was peeled off,

102
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:56,350
the person

103
00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:57,480
must still be alive.

104
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,680
So here comes the question.

105
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:02,220
Adjutant Zhang,

106
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:05,950
I wonder if you also have

107
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,890
any beautiful tattoos on your body.

108
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:10,570
Kill him.

109
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:19,300
Kill him.

110
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:29,220
I wonder if you felt guilty

111
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:32,530
when you peeled off the skin.

112
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,060
Did you feel that killing a person was
the same as killing a pig?

113
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,720
Some people have physiological reactions

114
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:43,070
when they kill humans.

115
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:47,060
Do you have any?

116
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,180
Come out.

117
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:22,530
I've been immune
to poisons and drugs since I was little.

118
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:23,620
Your drugs

119
00:07:25,670 --> 00:07:26,620
can't work on me.

120
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,700
What...

121
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:19,470
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

122
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:22,600
[Episode 24]

123
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,030
Sister! Sister!

124
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,400
Sister! Sister!

125
00:09:47,690 --> 00:09:48,280
Sister!

126
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:53,560
Sister...

127
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:56,460
Chief,

128
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,590
something went wrong at the inn.

129
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,650
Choose how you want to die,

130
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:29,180
and I will make that happen.

131
00:12:06,290 --> 00:12:06,960
Hurry!

132
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,400
Everyone, pull back into the fortress!

133
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:50,930
The Phoenix Fortress is on fire?

134
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,930
Everyone, find a way
to shake off the soldiers immediately

135
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:05,990
and retreat into the secret passage.

136
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:24,230
Commander,

137
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,820
we can't find the bandits.

138
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:28,250
There's a secret passage here.

139
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,710
I've figured out its approximate location.

140
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:32,650
I'll draw the map for you.

141
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:54,790
Come out!

142
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:55,880
You guys!

143
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:56,430
Get down.

144
00:13:56,890 --> 00:13:57,420
Get down!

145
00:13:57,430 --> 00:13:58,090
Don't move!

146
00:13:59,100 --> 00:13:59,630
Hurry up!

147
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:05,180
Everyone in the secret passage, come out!

148
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:05,840
Otherwise,

149
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,980
I won't leave any of them alive!

150
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:13,040
Let them go!

151
00:14:29,180 --> 00:14:30,160
Little girl,

152
00:14:31,050 --> 00:14:32,820
are you the Chief?

153
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:34,440
I am the Chief!

154
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,050
Look at her.

155
00:15:23,170 --> 00:15:25,030
You all should learn from her.

156
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:26,390
She's a mere chief of a fortress

157
00:15:26,390 --> 00:15:27,520
and a little girl,

158
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:28,980
yet she's so insightful.

159
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:33,520
She knew that if she shot me dead,

160
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:36,530
everyone in her fortress would get killed.

161
00:15:37,530 --> 00:15:39,590
Then you must understand this logic.

162
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:42,370
Killing is very simple.

163
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,340
But there are many issues that

164
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:47,070
matter much more than killing.

165
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:49,240
I don't want it to end up like this.

166
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,390
Your men killed my men first.

167
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:55,130
This is not like Nanqiang's way
of treating guests.

168
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,310
I will ask you a question.

169
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:58,820
If you answer me,

170
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:01,960
you can save the lives
of everyone in your fortress.

171
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:11,560
So you'd better answer me carefully.

172
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,880
Don't listen to his crap, Chief!

173
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:17,910
Son...

174
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:18,940
Bro!

175
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,100
What should we do?

176
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,120
Son...

177
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,420
My son...

178
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:42,920
What is your question?

179
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:43,490
Good.

180
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,290
Here's my question. There is a man

181
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,350
in a mask

182
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,930
who is super good at fighting,

183
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,150
like seriously

184
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:54,660
not even human-level good.

185
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:57,070
Do you know his whereabouts?

186
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:10,230
I haven't seen anyone like this.

187
00:17:27,349 --> 00:17:30,550
My intuition is very accurate.

188
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:32,550
She

189
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,730
didn't lie.

190
00:17:40,290 --> 00:17:41,420
So it's fine now.

191
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:43,890
It's fine.

192
00:17:44,890 --> 00:17:45,690
You may leave.

193
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:49,280
I mean, take the people
of your fortress and leave.

194
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:52,680
I just need

195
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,430
to borrow this fortress, okay?

196
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:56,510
Go!

197
00:19:19,940 --> 00:19:21,270
I'll kill you!

198
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:27,160
Commander.

199
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:30,450
You didn't keep your word.

200
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,690
What's the difference
between you and those bandits?

201
00:19:32,690 --> 00:19:34,020
There's no difference.

202
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,110
Well, there is one thing.

203
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:37,160
It's that I am smarter than them.

204
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:38,950
You see, if I were her just now,

205
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:40,800
I would have definitely grabbed the gun

206
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:41,990
and shot me.

207
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:43,670
With the leaderless enemy,

208
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,370
at least there would be a glimmer of hope.

209
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:47,480
Look, now they've fallen into my hands,
and they're done for.

210
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,610
Look at our soldiers

211
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,410
and their men.

212
00:19:50,610 --> 00:19:53,240
There's absolutely no difference.

213
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,790
Aren't they just a bunch of lunatics?

214
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:59,210
Dangle a bit of temptation
in front of anyone,

215
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:01,350
and they will risk their lives for you.

216
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:02,330
That's why

217
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:04,470
we must

218
00:20:04,690 --> 00:20:08,780
maintain their brutal animal nature
like this

219
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:11,890
and offer temptation at the right time

220
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:13,030
to satisfy them.

221
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,410
I am good at this sort of thing,

222
00:20:15,580 --> 00:20:16,150
so

223
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:17,510
I can become a dominant figure

224
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:19,050
in these troubled times.

225
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:20,300
I think today is

226
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:22,010
the perfect time

227
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:23,650
to let their animal nature

228
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,810
run free.

229
00:20:26,570 --> 00:20:28,590
This is my reason for killing.

230
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:30,480
What's your reason for killing?

231
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:56,250
So brutal.

232
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:21,330
Mo Yungao.

233
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,590
Why did he also come to Nanqiang?

234
00:22:18,510 --> 00:22:19,910
Take the secret passage.

235
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:12,980
Behave yourself!

236
00:23:13,230 --> 00:23:14,020
Don't move!

237
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,920
They are the ones at fault,

238
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:01,440
not you.

239
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:04,150
You must live.

240
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:16,900
You bastard!

241
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:26,660
Brother...

242
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:27,680
Brother!

243
00:25:33,870 --> 00:25:34,660
Brother!

244
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:28,950
Hurry up.

245
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:30,100
It's in the room ahead.

246
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:31,100
Keep up, quickly!

247
00:26:52,810 --> 00:26:53,440
-Go!
-Go!

248
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,070
Hurry up!

249
00:27:08,310 --> 00:27:08,920
Quickly!

250
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:31,890
Shrimpie...

251
00:28:22,750 --> 00:28:25,680
Fate brings people together
no matter the distance.

252
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:31,880
It should be this way.

253
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:41,680
I want to go back.

254
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:44,110
Going back now is a suicide act.

255
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:45,240
Where there's life,

256
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:46,360
there's hope.

257
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:48,080
If we don't have a chance now,

258
00:28:48,110 --> 00:28:49,770
will we have one in the future?

259
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:50,910
Xiao'er is dead.

260
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:52,920
Great Golden Blade is dead.

261
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:54,090
Everyone is dead.

262
00:28:55,770 --> 00:28:57,770
You run first. We'll cover the rear.

263
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:58,590
Run now.

264
00:28:59,030 --> 00:29:00,010
You guys go.

265
00:29:03,910 --> 00:29:05,020
Take care, sister.

266
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:06,360
See you in Bailejing.

267
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,020
Go quickly.

268
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:11,920
This way.

269
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:43,110
Let's go.

270
00:29:49,380 --> 00:29:51,040
It's the sign of the Archives.

271
00:30:02,330 --> 00:30:04,130
"When you think there's no way out,

272
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:05,930
a mighty army will come to help."

273
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:07,850
This is what you mentioned,

274
00:30:07,850 --> 00:30:09,510
the Zhang family in Nanqiang?

275
00:30:09,810 --> 00:30:12,140
It seems
that there are quite a lot of them.

276
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:15,700
Let's get out of here first.

277
00:30:15,700 --> 00:30:16,220
Okay.

278
00:30:29,090 --> 00:30:30,350
There's nowhere to go.

279
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,310
Smoke.

280
00:30:33,770 --> 00:30:35,830
You're craving a smoke at the moment?

281
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:38,310
Wait a minute!

282
00:30:39,570 --> 00:30:41,030
You didn't even say a word,

283
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:42,960
yet you chased us this far.

284
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:44,820
You all have good stamina, huh?

285
00:30:45,230 --> 00:30:46,350
There's no way out anyway.

286
00:30:46,350 --> 00:30:47,290
There's no need to rush it.

287
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:48,290
Take your breath.

288
00:30:48,570 --> 00:30:49,530
I will perform

289
00:30:49,730 --> 00:30:50,790
a show for you guys!

290
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,720
You people from the Zhang family
are quite interesting.

291
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,090
But sometimes you are way too confident

292
00:30:58,090 --> 00:30:59,350
in your capabilities.

293
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:01,230
In this situation,

294
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:02,960
you are still struggling?

295
00:31:03,580 --> 00:31:04,790
As the old saying goes,

296
00:31:04,790 --> 00:31:06,140
nothing ventured,

297
00:31:06,380 --> 00:31:07,790
nothing gained!

298
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:21,220
A flare shot into the sky

299
00:31:21,330 --> 00:31:23,720
summons a mighty army to come.

300
00:31:24,180 --> 00:31:25,750
Who summoned me?

301
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:29,240
The Zhang family's Southern Archives!

302
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:36,960
Then who are you guys?

303
00:31:38,350 --> 00:31:39,660
Why is it just you?

304
00:31:40,090 --> 00:31:41,560
Where is the "mighty army"
of the Zhang family?

305
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:42,460
It's me.

306
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:43,420
I am

307
00:31:43,490 --> 00:31:45,820
Zhang Qianjunwanma (means mighty army).

308
00:31:53,770 --> 00:31:56,310
Is the Zhang family
so unreliable in Bailejing?

309
00:31:56,310 --> 00:31:57,760
You'll get us all killed!

310
00:31:58,090 --> 00:32:00,890
I'm the one
who's going to be killed because of you.

311
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,750
If I had known
it'd summon such a useless guy to come,

312
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:04,210
we wouldn't have bothered

313
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:05,590
wasting so much time there.

314
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:06,790
Are you done talking?

315
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,090
Will you ever stop?

316
00:32:09,450 --> 00:32:10,870
It's your first time in Bailejing.

317
00:32:10,870 --> 00:32:12,480
As a local member of the Zhang family,

318
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,210
I must fulfill my duty as a host.

319
00:32:15,710 --> 00:32:16,940
Take it easy, please.

320
00:32:18,540 --> 00:32:19,370
Take this!

321
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:26,700
Go after them!

322
00:32:34,100 --> 00:32:35,020
Go that way!

323
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,260
You're not good at fighting,

324
00:33:12,260 --> 00:33:13,880
but you sure can run.

325
00:33:16,060 --> 00:33:16,860
Come with me.

326
00:33:17,310 --> 00:33:18,910
They won't catch us for sure.

327
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:40,960
What is this place?

328
00:33:43,450 --> 00:33:45,340
This is where my mentor and I live.

329
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:48,530
It's also where the Zhang family is
stationed in Nanqiang.

330
00:33:48,530 --> 00:33:49,340
Your mentor?

331
00:34:12,030 --> 00:34:12,889
Little Taoist,

332
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:15,170
what was that amazing sorcery

333
00:34:15,510 --> 00:34:17,860
you just used?

334
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,449
It's divine magic.

335
00:34:20,790 --> 00:34:22,730
I've been in this temple
with my mentor since I was a child,

336
00:34:22,730 --> 00:34:24,610
practicing the Five Ghosts Delivery.

337
00:34:24,610 --> 00:34:26,739
I've already mastered it thoroughly.

338
00:34:26,820 --> 00:34:27,780
Divine magic?

339
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:30,500
Does our Zhang family
have this secret technique?

340
00:34:30,500 --> 00:34:31,900
It's just a trick.

341
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:34,300
This Little Taoist conjured a fire dragon

342
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:36,300
just in order to distract the enemy.

343
00:34:36,530 --> 00:34:38,000
But he was so fast

344
00:34:38,130 --> 00:34:39,730
that even you didn't notice.

345
00:34:39,820 --> 00:34:40,940
What do you know?

346
00:34:41,210 --> 00:34:42,610
The Five Ghosts Delivery

347
00:34:42,610 --> 00:34:44,540
can move everything in this world.

348
00:34:44,730 --> 00:34:45,790
As long as I want to,

349
00:34:46,210 --> 00:34:47,449
I can even move

350
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:49,610
this temple away overnight.

351
00:34:51,780 --> 00:34:54,239
Zhang Qianzhang
taught you all this, right?

352
00:34:59,530 --> 00:35:00,730
You know my mentor?

353
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:04,390
Who on earth are you?

354
00:35:05,070 --> 00:35:05,880
This is

355
00:35:05,940 --> 00:35:08,480
the former Director
of our Southern Archives,

356
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:09,360
Zhang Haiqi.

357
00:35:20,940 --> 00:35:21,900
My mentor's wife...

